f=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=64.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Grrr Druids...</span><hr size=1> I hate druids that are smart enough to outheal the nukes =)<br><br>First things first, WD is kinda like splurt. All the damage comes at the end. That being said make sure you cancel magic it off you. Yes this means you need to have your top two buff slots open but I'm sure you already know that. A fairly decent strategy is to shock em when they start healing because it interupts close to %100 of the time. Between shocks hit em with your best nukes. It is a good idea to golem wand the druid before you start in on them as they have a ton of buffs and you don't want them zipping away from you.<br><br>The bad news is unless you are lvl 60 if a druid decides to just take your nukes and outheal them you will be in some serious trouble. The good news is they wont be able to kill you either so it is kind of a stalemate. Go wait for that druid to finish his quad then wand him and nuke him into the ground. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uauroreakengro.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aurore Akengro</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/12/02 2:24:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=64.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Grrr Druids...</span><hr size=1> The only thing I try against druids is sunstrike followed by ice spear. This has a chance of taking them out. If not, then just gate <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Aurore<HR>~Seekers of Divinity~<BR>Sorceress of <a href=http://www.ralloszek.net>Rallos Zek</a><BR><a href=http://www.progressquest.com><img src=http://www-rocq.inria.fr/~bnguyen/pony.gif></img></a>The Pony with the Pointy Hat.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ufrosthoundsz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>FrosthoundSZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/12/02 3:37:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=64.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~scoventon/EQ/fh.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Grrr Druids...</span><hr size=1> Druids freak out when they can't run away, so carry golem wands to dispell them. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uzackaresh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zackaresh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/12/02 5:21:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=64.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Grrr Druids...</span><hr size=1> I'm 56 Aurore. Lvl 60 Wiz pvp is a different story.<br>Where drop golem wands now? <p>Zackaresh Darkfire<BR>Avatar of Solusek Ro<BR>Officer of Die letze Zuflucht<BR>Rallos Zek<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uauroreakengro.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aurore Akengro</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/12/02 7:52:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=64.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Grrr Druids...</span><hr size=1> Just gate then, time plays for the druids advantage. No use chasing after them. Unless you can kill them in the first 10-20 seconds or so you aren't going to make it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uneyfearsthe2nd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Neyfears The2nd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/12/02 12:41:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=64.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Try this</span><hr size=1> Rains..<br><br>If he is prepared, golem his Circles off of him, or your rains won't do alot..<br><br>It forces him to move mid heal ..or outdamages the heals..the best is the 59 tears of prexus.  I had a 60 cleric decide to nuke me last night..as he started to cast, I had already started my rain..his Magic based spell was absorbed by my spellshield, after 1 rain, 1 lure..he was dead. <br><br>This works well for most healing classes..they will try to stand next to you if smart.  Keep an eye out for the cast message, stop running, hit a rain spell or an interupt.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ullyapakadeabn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Llyap aka Deabn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/13/02 3:55:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=64.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> well</span><hr size=1> I am only 33, but so far 20pp pumice&gt;druid dots.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udarkudaos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>darkudaos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/27/02 3:11:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=64.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: well</span><hr size=1> Golem wand/pumice the little tree hugger till he falls from the sky (soe), then watch him panic as he tries to heal, mem, recast soe and get out of range all at once. have all resists up, dispell ro's and WD as they land, have 2 open slots and 2 junk buffs below them, (in case you are dispelled first off) if only dot/debuff is on you chuck a click buff up and pumice/dispell self, so that you dont eat into your real buffs. They can't dot you to death if you pumice fast, and they cant nuke you to death if you pumice fast. But unless you are prepared (sow included) and near to FM (will need it to outlast the heals), gate. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showPrevMessage?topicID=64.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showNextMessage?topicID=64.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=64.topic&index=8><img src=http://www.gra